description:
The Bible teaches that speaking in tongues is one of the gifts of the Holy Spirit. But does the Bible teach that speaking in tongues is proof of the baptism of the Holy Spirit? What are the signs of being filled with the Holy Spirit? Is being slain in the Spirit an example of Holy Spirit power?

Walter Veith compares the contemporary Pentecostal movement with the disciples experiences at Pentecost and afterward. What does the Bible teach about the gifts of the Holy Spirit, such as speaking in tongues? Did God give the gift of tongues as a sign of the baptism of the Holy Spirit?  Why did Jesus promise to send the Holy Spirit? What does the Bible say is the function of the Holy Spirit? For what purpose did God give the gifts of the Holy Spirit? Discover Bible what the Bible teaches about these things.
This presentation also examines some of the most famous of the Pentecostal preachers, comparing their doctrinal statements with the Word of God. What is the basis of the charismatic revival and power religion? What is the history of the modern charismatic movement? What has contemporary Pentecostalism got in common with ancient cult religions? A comparative chart shows the similarities and differences between spiritual manifestations in different religions and in the early Christian church. Surprising details are revealed about the gifts of the Holy Spirit in an in-depth study of 1 Corinthians 14.

This is an eye-opening Bible study and examination of the contemporary charismatic movement, with a focus on speaking in tongues and gifts of the Holy Spirit. Take a new look at what the Bible really teaches about speaking in tongues.

Discover more: http://amazingdiscoveries.org/
